		<div class="comment-body"><p>Cloud computing is basically having everything as a service, not a product. See more here:<br />
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cloud_computing" rel="nofollow">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cloud_computing</a><br />
My objection is that they also want everyone to put all their data in &#8220;the cloud&#8221;. Just how secure do we all think that is, in terms of access by federal government, hackers, with a single keystroke. Personally, I think it&#8217;s a BIG potential threat to privacy. Bottom line, you will be in for a lifetime subscription when/if the cloud becomes the norm.</p>
